vidence. Susan Harrison also offers a summary of the innovative tools that have been developed and used in California to conserve and protect this stunning and imperiled diversity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEndemic animals -- California. 0aEndemic animals -- Conservation -- California. 0aEndemic animals -- Ecology -- California. 0aEndemic animalsxConservationzCalifornia. 0aEndemic animalsxEcologyzCalifornia. 0aEndemic animalszCalifornia. 0aEndemic plants -- California. 0aEndemic plants -- Conservation -- California. 0aEndemic plants -- Ecology -- California. 0aEndemic plantsxConservationzCalifornia. 0aEndemic plantsxEcologyzCalifornia. 0aEndemic plantszCalifornia. 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095473140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520954731423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520954731/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles